concept_universal_solver
  term "universal solver"
  intent concept_lookup
  category algorithm
  aliases "the universal solver|universal problem solver"
  summary "The universal solver is formal-ai's deterministic 11-step loop: impulse, formalization, context, history, decomposition, TDD, synthesis, combination, verification, simplification, documentation. Every interface routes through the same loop."
  source docs/case-studies/issue-12/README.md
  source_kind project-docs
concept_event_log
  term "event log"
  intent concept_lookup
  category data-structure
  aliases "the event log|eventlog|append-only log"
  summary "The event log is formal-ai's append-only system of record. Every step in the universal solver loop appends an Event with a stable content-addressed id; the user-facing answer is, by construction, a projection of this log."
  source docs/NON-GOALS.md
  source_kind project-docs
concept_links_notation
  term "Links Notation"
  intent concept_lookup
  category data-format
  aliases "links notation|lino|the links notation format"
  summary "Links Notation is an indentation-based, untyped serialization format used by the Deep Theory project to represent links and link networks as portable text."
  source "https://github.com/linksplatform/Documentation"
  source_kind project-docs
concept_links_meta_theory
  term "Links meta-theory"
  intent concept_lookup
  category knowledge-representation
  aliases "links meta-theory|the links meta-theory|links theory|the links theory|link theory|theory of links|deep theory|deep theory of links|теория связей|теории связей|теорию связей|теория связи|глубокая теория связей|глубокой теории связей|глубокую теорию связей|метатеория связей|мета-теория связей|लिंक्स सिद्धांत|लिंक सिद्धांत|लिंक्स मेटा-सिद्धांत|डीप थ्योरी|संबंधों का सिद्धांत|链接元理论|链接理论|Links理论|Deep Theory|链接的理论|深度链接理论"
  summary "In the Link Foundation context, links theory means the link-foundation/meta-theory repository and its archived Links Theory articles. It describes information representation through links: references to links, with the compact set-theory projection L -> L^2. In formal-ai, a bare question about links theory assumes this product; if you mean another similarly named theory, specify the domain because those theories are described differently."
  source "https://github.com/link-foundation/meta-theory"
  source_kind official-repository
  localized en
    term "Links meta-theory"
    aliases "links meta-theory|the links meta-theory|links theory|the links theory|link theory|theory of links|deep theory|deep theory of links"
    summary "In the Link Foundation context, links theory means the link-foundation/meta-theory repository and its archived Links Theory articles. It describes information representation through links: references to links, with the compact set-theory projection L -> L^2. In formal-ai, a bare question about links theory assumes this product; if you mean another similarly named theory, specify the domain because those theories are described differently."
    source "https://github.com/link-foundation/meta-theory"
    source_kind official-repository
  localized ru
    term "Теория связей"
    aliases "теория связей|теории связей|теорию связей|теория связи|глубокая теория связей|глубокой теории связей|глубокую теорию связей|метатеория связей|мета-теория связей"
    summary "В контексте Link Foundation «теория связей» означает репозиторий link-foundation/meta-theory и архивированные статьи о Links Theory. Она описывает представление информации через связи: ссылки на связи, с компактной проекцией в теории множеств L -> L^2. В formal-ai такой запрос по умолчанию относится к этому продукту; если имеется в виду другая теория с похожим названием, укажите область, потому что другие теории описываются иначе."
    source "https://github.com/link-foundation/meta-theory"
    source_kind official-repository
  localized hi
    term "लिंक्स मेटा-सिद्धांत"
    aliases "लिंक्स सिद्धांत|लिंक सिद्धांत|लिंक्स मेटा-सिद्धांत|डीप थ्योरी|संबंधों का सिद्धांत"
    summary "Link Foundation संदर्भ में links theory का अर्थ link-foundation/meta-theory रिपॉजिटरी और Links Theory लेखों का संग्रह है. यह सूचना को links के माध्यम से दर्शाता है: links पर references, compact set-theory projection L -> L^2 के साथ. formal-ai में links theory पर साधारण प्रश्न इसी उत्पाद को मानता है; यदि समान नाम वाली कोई दूसरी theory चाहिए तो domain बताएं."
    source "https://github.com/link-foundation/meta-theory"
    source_kind official-repository
  localized zh
    term 链接元理论
    aliases "链接元理论|链接理论|Links理论|Deep Theory|链接的理论|深度链接理论"
    summary "在 Link Foundation 语境中, links theory 指 link-foundation/meta-theory 仓库及其归档的 Links Theory 文章. 它用链接来表示信息: 指向链接的引用, 并带有紧凑的集合论投影 L -> L^2. 在 formal-ai 中, 对 links theory 的裸问题默认指这个项目; 如果指另一个同名理论, 请说明领域."
    source "https://github.com/link-foundation/meta-theory"
    source_kind official-repository
concept_graph
  term Graph
  intent concept_lookup
  category knowledge-representation
  aliases "graph|graphs|graph theory|граф|графы|теория графов|графовой структуры|ग्राफ|ग्राफ़|ग्राफ सिद्धांत|ग्राफ थ्योरी|图|图论|圖|圖論"
  summary "A graph is a mathematical structure made of vertices and edges, where edges relate pairs of vertices. Through Link Foundation meta-theory, a Links Notation links network can represent any graph while also allowing links to link to links. That avoids treating knowledge as two artificial classes of vertices and edges; in many common graph definitions, edges between edges are not allowed."
  source "https://github.com/link-foundation/meta-theory"
  source_kind official-repository
  localized en
    term Graph
    aliases "graph|graphs|graph theory"
    summary "A graph is a mathematical structure made of vertices and edges, where edges relate pairs of vertices. Through Link Foundation meta-theory, a Links Notation links network can represent any graph while also allowing links to link to links. That avoids treating knowledge as two artificial classes of vertices and edges; in many common graph definitions, edges between edges are not allowed."
    source "https://github.com/link-foundation/meta-theory"
    source_kind official-repository
  localized ru
    term Граф
    aliases "граф|графы|теория графов|графовая структура|графовой структуры"
    summary "Граф — математическая структура из вершин и ребер, где ребра связывают пары вершин. В контексте Link Foundation meta-theory и Links Notation сеть связей может представить любой граф, а также позволяет ссылкам ссылаться на ссылки. Поэтому Links Notation не ограничивает знание искусственным разделением на вершины и ребра: в популярных определениях графов ребра между ребрами обычно не допускаются."
    source "https://github.com/link-foundation/meta-theory"
    source_kind official-repository
  localized hi
    term ग्राफ
    aliases "ग्राफ|ग्राफ़|ग्राफ सिद्धांत|ग्राफ थ्योरी"
    summary "ग्राफ शीर्षों और किनारों से बनी गणितीय संरचना है, जहाँ किनारे शीर्षों के जोड़ों को जोड़ते हैं. Link Foundation meta-theory और Links Notation के संदर्भ में links network किसी भी graph को व्यक्त कर सकता है और links को links से जोड़ने देता है. इससे ज्ञान को vertices और edges की दो कृत्रिम श्रेणियों में बाँधने की जरूरत नहीं रहती; कई प्रचलित graph परिभाषाओं में edges between edges की अनुमति नहीं होती."
    source "https://github.com/link-foundation/meta-theory"
    source_kind official-repository
  localized zh
    term 图
    aliases "图|图论|圖|圖論"
    summary "图是由顶点和边组成的数学结构, 边连接成对的顶点. 在 Link Foundation meta-theory 和 Links Notation 语境中, 链接网络可以表示任何图, 也允许链接指向链接. 因此 Links Notation 不必把知识人为拆成顶点和边两类; 许多常见图定义通常不允许边连接边."
    source "https://github.com/link-foundation/meta-theory"
    source_kind official-repository
concept_doublet
  term doublet
  intent concept_lookup
  category data-structure
  aliases "doublet link|a doublet|two-link"
  summary "A doublet is a link with exactly two endpoints. In Deep Theory it is the canonical reduction target for higher-arity links because every higher arity can be encoded as a chain of doublets."
  source docs/VISION.md
  source_kind project-docs
